	   <tr><td colspan=2>Vendor in EC as previously said. <br><br>Summon Companion: CotH pet summon. Level 39. Bad news is it won't bring your pet to you if he's on ANY hate list. Good thing is it's only 50 mana, and a relatively fast 5.0 cast time. makes us actually usefull in no pet zones like the beginning of Velketor's Labyrinth. Pet will return to spot if /pet guard here is used, so for pet dragging use the good ole /pet sit down. Now maybe they can change our crappy PoG bracer effect to this spell rather than the 900,145th item we have with reclaim energy.<br><br>Expedience: Pet SoW. Level 29. 20ish% great for those of you with JBoots for inverse pet kiting. Silly me forgot to check if it worked indoors though, to chase down those damnable indoor sowed mobs. <br><br>Valiant Companion: Makes pet Immune to Fear spells. its level 59 though... Should be 44. It still makes me go petless against Foxy Voxy. I will get an eyepatch. oh yes, I will. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
