<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98279888019633></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98279888019633><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98279888019633>RE: Ice Of Velious</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98279888019633#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=999><span id=Sage>Salenie</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>22 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 21st 6:41 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You hardly need go to the that frozen wasteland to find its ice.  The continent may be newly discovered, but it's ice can be found anywhere.  Simply hunt with parties those creatures which, at your current level of ability, that would seem to dispatch you easily should you try on your own.  They collect this useful substance.<br><br>One place I found the ice in a strange concentration is in the crag spiders of East Karanas.  We are not talking hugely common, but perhaps appearing in one in 40 or so.  I would not hunt these if I were you alone, but if you can find stalwart friends they should be good for your purposes.<br><br>Lastly, you could try asking your more established colleagues if they have any.  I know I have nearly a score of the things collecting dust in the vaults of Felwithe.  Any magician that actually researches her own spell probably has quite a hoard of these things squirreled away.<br><br>I hope this advice helps you, sister.  Good luck in your research.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Salenie Mithrilweaver<br>Clan Battle Axe (www.clanbattleaxe.com)<br>High Elf 53rd Magician - EMarr</td></tr>
