	   <tr><td colspan=2>I always hated it how people would have necromancer vs. magician and magician vs. wizard arguments. It seemed to have calmed down and everyone finally got the idea that they were all pretty good, until Christmas. Then a bunch of people got the game and knew nothing about it and the arguments started again. However, I will answer your question anyway.<br><br>1. None of them are the 'best'. They all are better or worse than each other in different situations. Wizards are VERY much needed when it comes to non-velious uber mobs. Magicians are very good in dungeons when you need a lot of damage over time and for when you are getting a lot of quick pulls that die in 20-30 seconds. Necromancers are very versatile and can do a little of everything when in a group, but they mainly server as damage dealers. When you need damage over time and the fights are a bit longer, necromancers are just as efficient as magicians.<br><br>2. In a high level duel between the classes ANY of them. Could win. The biggest part of who would win the duel is who the best player is. Necromancers are very good at dueling becuase of having fear, snare, powerful DoTs, AND a pet. However it could also be said that a magician with their powerful pets and good DD's are very good duelists. Then of course you have the wizards who can do quick DD's, stun you, and shadow step all over. Although truthfully, in a high level duel the necromancer and wizard have an edge over the magician becuase they have damage shields and the magician doesn't. Of course it really all depends on how good the players are at dueling. It also depends on the terrain of where you are fighting(indoor, outdoor, wide open, hilly, etc.).<br><br>3. As for soloing the necromancer is the best. However magicians are also VERY good soloers and wizards are good soloers once they get to level 29 and get their snare spell.<br><br>Truthfully, I think you should play a magician. They are the easiest of the three to play as a newbie. Also, it really doesn't matter how well a class can solo. Grouping is(usually) much more efficient and fun. Although it IS nice to be able to solo well for those times when your group consists of bad players or when you can't find a group. The most important thing I can tell you is to not worry too much about leveling and have fun. Try roleplaying or just helping out a person randomly. Or try adventuring around and looking at the world that the coders created. It is really very nice and there is a lot to see. <br><br>Former player of:<br><br>Zuranthium Spellcrafter &lt;The Elitists&gt; - Level 50 Gnome Magician of The Tribunal Server.<br>Corpusnuntia Nimtathan &lt;Valorguard&gt; - Level 40 Erudite Necromancer of The Nameless Server.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
