	   <tr><td colspan=2>I never knew Dwarves could be magicians....In any case try the Hermit in Lake Rathe or Crushbone. Crushbone is a nice little newbie dungeon that you should enjoy. The hermit is good for soloing, but the money sucks and if its already camped when you get there you will have to resort to killing aviaks that are near the arena(the LITTLE ones, not the guards).<br><br>The dual siren spawn that you will find on the rocks when you take the boat from FP to BB is also a very nice solo spot for your level.<br><br>Oasis is also a decent group spot for exp. However there are a lot of high level monsters getting trained around and the loot sucks.<br><br>Wisps are very nice but you might want to try something....well, simpler first.<br><br>Also since your a Dwarf there is a very nice spot in Kaladim to fight things where only Dwarf magicians can go. Find the banker in Kaladim and tpye in "Hi how are you today kind banker". To do this trick you can't press the enter bar before you talk to him. After you say that to him you will be transported to a secret spot in the city where a dark elf is chained up and can be killed very easily and will take you all the way to level 20 and get you a lot of money.<br><br>Have fun. Don't forget that last hunting spot I mentioned.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
